{
  "stem": "6052.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But at a later point, we lived all together in-- at one-- at one place while it was before in the [?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Humboldtstrasse, ?] which-- I-- the house she owned when my grandfather died.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Later, we lived in the Nordstrasse 27.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And to backtrack a little bit, what happened-- or what happened when I was a youngster, I went to school, and it was seemingly everything pretty normal.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I remember the great names like Felix Mendelssohn.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was an [INAUDIBLE], a monument erected from him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When the Nazis came, and after it stood already for 44 years, it disappeared overnight because they tried and they successfully erased all the background of Jews-- of poets, of composers, and so on.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember Heinrich Heine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "This name might-- might be known to many people over the world.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was a composer of a famous song, which is still-- which was still sung in Germany, saying [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this means I still don't know why I'm so sad and what the meaning is of it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This is-- when people go on the Reine and travel on the Reine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This Heinrich Heine wrote a lot of beautiful poetry and the songs were created.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And since he was a Jew, they did not mention him anymore, but his song was still used.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE] there were many poets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Stefan Zweig, I remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I read Stefan Zweig-- was an outstanding, an outstanding writer, and he committed suicide when he saw what is going to come.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He could not live anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I believe this was with his wife-- his wife and he died in Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then, I remember the day I went to the Yiddish-- to the [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Polish ?] consulate, a Polish consulate.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
